  "title": "Click Analytics - images don't send data",
  "body": "Hi. I found a weird problem. \r\nThis is my listener: \r\n\r\n```js\r\ndocument.addEventListener('click', (e) => {\r\n  \r\n  if (e.target.matches('.click-analytics')) {\r\n    let correct_position = 1 + parseInt(e.target.getAttribute('data-position'));\r\n    window.aa('click', {\r\n      objectID: e.target.getAttribute('data-objectid'),\r\n      position: correct_position,\r\n    })\r\n    console.log(e.target.getAttribute('data-objectid'));\r\n  } \r\n  else if (e.target.matches('.conversion-analytics')) {\r\n    window.aa('conversion', {\r\n      objectID: e.target.getAttribute('data-objectid'),\r\n    })\r\n    console.log(e.target.getAttribute('data-objectid'));\r\n  }\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nthat is part of my hit template: \r\n ```html\r\n<div class=\"hit-content\">\r\n              <div class=\"hit-image\">\r\n                <a class=\"click-analytics\" data-objectid=\"{{objectID}}\" data-position=\"{{__hitIndex}}\" href=\"{{url}}\"><img src=\"{{image}}\" alt=\"{{name}}\"></a>\r\n              </div>\r\n              <a class=\"click-analytics\" data-objectid=\"{{objectID}}\" data-position=\"{{__hitIndex}}\" href=\"{{url}}\">lalals</a>\r\n                <h2 class=\"hit-name\"><a class=\"click-analytics\" data-objectid=\"{{objectID}}\" data-position=\"{{__hitIndex}}\" href=\"{{url}}\">{{name}}</a></h2> \r\n```\r\nAnd the problem is:\r\nWhen i click on .hit-name or div with \"lalals\" text. It seems work well. I got console message: `91722`\r\nBut when i click on image (.hit-image) it doesn't work. (i don't get console.log message).\r\n",
